# 10.03 Architecture Reference

## Overview

The Architecture Reference provides a technical reference for the core architecture of cmdOS.

This document explains how major system components interact to transform human intent into real-world execution.

The purpose is to provide a unified architectural understanding for:

- Engineers
- Developers
- Researchers
- Contributors

Core principle:

Intent

↓

Intelligence

↓

Agents

↓

Capabilities

↓

Execution

↓

Digital Environment

---

# 1. cmdOS Architecture Overview

cmdOS is designed as an AI-native operating system architecture.

Traditional operating systems focus on managing:

- Applications
- Files
- Hardware resources

cmdOS focuses on managing:

- Human intent
- AI intelligence
- Agents
- Capabilities
- Execution workflows

High-level architecture:

```
User

↓

Intent Interface

↓

AI Intelligence Layer

↓

Agent Layer

↓

Capability Layer

↓

Execution Runtime

↓

Digital Environment
```

---

# 2. Architecture Layers

cmdOS consists of multiple interconnected layers.

---

# 2.1 Intent Layer

## Purpose

The Intent Layer is the human interaction layer.

It receives user goals expressed through natural language.

Input methods:

- Text
- Voice
- Visual interaction
- Commands

Responsibilities:

- Receive user requests
- Understand desired outcomes
- Extract goals and requirements

Example:

User:

"Prepare my weekly business report."

The Intent Layer identifies:

- Objective
- Context
- Expected result

---

# 2.2 Intelligence Layer

## Purpose

The Intelligence Layer provides AI understanding and reasoning.

Responsibilities:

- Intent recognition
- Context analysis
- Planning
- Decision making

Components:

- AI Router
- Language Models
- Reasoning Engine
- Context Engine
- Memory System

---

# 2.3 Agent Layer

## Purpose

The Agent Layer provides autonomous AI entities capable of executing tasks.

Agents transform goals into actions.

Responsibilities:

- Understand objectives
- Create plans
- Select capabilities
- Execute workflows
- Verify results

Agent structure:

```
Agent

- Intelligence

- Memory

- Planning

- Capability Access

- Execution Control
```

---

# 2.4 Capability Layer

## Purpose

The Capability Layer provides executable abilities for Agents.

Capabilities connect AI Agents with external systems.

Examples:

- Email capability
- File management capability
- Database capability
- Browser capability
- API capability
- Application capability

Architecture:

```
Agent

↓

Capability

↓

External System

↓

Action
```

---

# 2.5 Execution Runtime

## Purpose

The Execution Runtime converts AI decisions into real operations.

Responsibilities:

- Execute actions
- Manage workflows
- Track progress
- Handle errors
- Recover failed tasks

Components:

- Task Manager
- Workflow Engine
- Execution Controller
- Recovery System

---

# 2.6 Environment Layer

## Purpose

The Environment Layer represents the digital world where cmdOS operates.

Supported environments:

## Desktop

Includes:

- Applications
- Files
- Operating system functions

---

## Mobile

Includes:

- Mobile applications
- Device functions
- Notifications

---

## Cloud

Includes:

- APIs
- Web services
- Cloud infrastructure

---

## Enterprise

Includes:

- Business systems
- Internal platforms
- Organization workflows

